<h2 id="hdr-top">About Skunk Labs</h2>


<p class="lead">
	Why Skunk Labs
</p>

<p>
	<strong>Skunk Labs</strong> was designed around the idea that skunkworks labs should require minimal lab management. Calling
	it a project management tool would be stretching the phrase.	Skunk Labs is a centralized place for individuals in the organization to
	come and seek help on their side project and to keep interested individuals informed.
</p>

<p>
	Skunk Labs is separated into two primary areas of functionality: <em>Skunk Labs Suggestions</em> and <em>Labs</em>.
</p>

<p>
	The Suggestions area is where you, as an ordinary employee, can make suggestions for improvements. This is similar to the concept of
	<em>ACT Teams</em>. You can make a suggestion and then a team of volunteers (the Suggestion Team) will attempt to guide it completion.
	You can "plus" an idea to vote for it and that will help indicate to the organization popular suggestions or ideas. It may also help if
	the suggestion requires management involvement or a budget.
</p>

<p>
	You can approach Labs in a similar manner. However the spirit of a lab is that you have an idea that you would like to implement
	on your spare time but need other people's assistance. These could be labs to create new internal tools to make your team's life better,
	to plan a training event to provide the department with an opportunity to use new technology, or to reassess the way work is done between
	cross-functional teams and attempt to fix it. The sky is the limit. With labs you propose the idea, define the roles  you will need to
	complete the lab, and then recruit (or wait for) people to work on it with you.
</p>

